        "text": "I'm excited to share that the community <https:\/\/feelingof.com\/the-name\/|renaming> is now complete. We're now the *Feeling of Computing*. We have a new domain, <http:\/\/feelingof.com|feelingof.com>. I've updated the logo, the podcast, a bunch of DNS stuff, and even the patreon (for people who really enjoy the podcast) which gets its own special url, <http:\/\/feelingoff.com|feelingoff.com> (since the podcast bonus feed is \"Feeling off Computing\").\n\nThere was a bit of poorly-timed DNS reworking today when Mariano's newsletter went out, so apologies if anyone clicked a broken link. Should be working now (though at the old domain – temporarily).\n\nIf you see anything else that looks unintentionally wrong \/ broken, please let me know and I'll attend to it.\n\nPhew! This was the second biggest \"long time coming\" issue to tackle. Now, onto the big one — getting off Slack. I'll talk more about that soon. Thanks everyone for your patience. If you ever have meta-level thoughts \/ feedback about the community, just post in <#CEXED56UR|administrivia> or send me a DM. :bow:",
